      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 8 September 1873. ¶  ¶ I have received another last letter from Giles, ¶ Ernest Giles; letter not found. ¶  ¶ noble friend. The dry season there makes it impossible for him to follow the ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">73.09.08a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 5. Nov. 1873' [Received 5 November 1873]. For a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>published version<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of this letter, see Voigt (1996), p.117-8.</p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">8/9/73.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich habe noch einen letzten Brief von Giles erhalten, edler Freund. Die dortige regenlose Jahreszeit macht es ihm unmöglich den Alberga aufwärts zu verfolgen, da nur noch Salz-Lachen darin sind. Er geht also den Stevenson Fluss hinauf, der ihn vielleicht ganz zum Olga-Gebirge führen wird. Mt Olga ist nur der Culminationspunkt eines grossen neuen Gebirges.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Seine Parthie besteht aus</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>H. Tietken</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alfr. Gibson</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jam<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Andrews</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">und ihm selbst als Befehligenden.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Er hat 24 Pferde, u kann nöthigen falls 1 Jahr das Feld behaupten soweit es seine Lebensmittel anlangt, wenn nicht ganz unvorhergesehene Unfälle eintreten.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Oberst Warburton, der von jenseits des Macdonnell-Gebirge operirt hat eine starke Parthie u dann noch den Vortheil des Gebrauchs von Dromedaren.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich hätte Giles gern besser unterstützt gesehen, vermochte es aber nicht mehr als £ 600 für ihn zusammen zu bringen. Es ist ein ebenso braver als muthiger u praktischer Mann. Lassen Sie uns das Beste für ihn u den Oberst hoffen. Zwei neue Linien von Ost zu West, werden alle künftigen Expeditionen leicht machen.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Die Idee, welche neulich nach 20 Jahren wieder in der geogr. Gesellsch. entwickelt wurde bezüglich warmer unter-oceanischer Quellen am Nordpol, ist nicht ohne Wahrscheinlichkeit u begünstigt Ihre Theorie eines offenen Pol-Meeres. Warum aber am<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Südpol</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">keine</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">warmen</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Quellen</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>existiren sollen ist unbegreiflich, wenn wir sogar einen Zeugen vulkanischer Thätigkeit dort im Mt Erebus haben. Können nicht auch andere Feuerschlünde näher dem Meerwasser sein u dort weit den Pol erwärmen?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">What follows is presented as a separate text in Voigt (1996), p. 119. It<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">a note writen by M on the back of an envelope addressed by him on the front<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>'Herrn Professor | Dr Aug. Petermann | Gotha |<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">Germany</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>|<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">Ferd von Mueller</hi>
                        </seg>' and postmarked 'Melbourne | 4 D | SE 10 | 73' and 'London } paid | 4 NO 73'. Like M’s letter, the envelope has been annotated by Petermann: 'Erh. 5. Nov. 1873' [Received 5 November 1873]; M’s letter had presumably been enclosed in it.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>Dr Sonder in Hamburg, der grosse Algenkenner u Forscher auch in Landpflanzen S. Afrikas u. Australiens, ist mein ältester u. theuerster<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Freund im Leben. Lassen Sie ja seinen Namen in Ihren Karten ja doch erscheinen.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8 September 1873.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have received another last letter from Giles,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles; letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>noble friend. The dry season there makes it impossible for him to follow the Alberga<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alberga Creek, SA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>upstream, as all that remains of it are pools of salt water. He is therefore going up the Stevenson River,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Stevenson Creek, SA.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which will perhaps take him all the way to the Olga Ranges.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mt Olga is now Kata Tjuta, NT.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mount Olga is only the culmination point of a large new mountain range.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>His party consists of:</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>H. Tietken<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. W. H. Tietkens.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Alfr. Gibson</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jam<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Andrews<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Andrews<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>born c.1855, died 1933 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Advertiser</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Adelaide),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>24 October 1933, p. 9), but no other life details found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">and Giles himself as commander.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He has 24 horses and can, if necessary, remain in the field for 1 year as far as his provisions are concerned, unless some totally unforeseen mishap should occur.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Colonel<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Warburton, who operates from beyond the MacDonnell Ranges, has a strong party and in addition the advantage of dromedaries.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Warburton and his party, after suffering extreme deprivation while crossing the Great Sandy Desert, eventually reached the Oakover River, WA, and thence the coast.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should have liked to see Giles better supported, but was unable to bring together more than £600 for him. He is as honest a man, as he is courageous and practical. Let us hope for the best for him and for the Colonel. Two new routes from east to west will make all future expeditions easy.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The idea, recently expanded on once again after 20 years in the Geographical Society concerning warm sub-oceanic springs at the North Pole,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Anderson (1872).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is not so improbable and favours your theory of an open Polar ocean. But it is incomprehensible, why<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">no such warm springs</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>should exist at the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">South Pole</hi>
               </seg>, when we even have a witness of volcanic activity there at Mount Erebus. Could there not also be other fiery abysses closer to the ocean there warming the Pole over large areas?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn10" n="11">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>note 2<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>above.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>Dr Sonder of Hamburg, the great algologist and also researcher of land plants of South Africa<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn11" n="12">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Harvey &amp;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sonder (1859-65).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and Australia, is the oldest and dearest friend in my life. Do make sure that his name does also appear in your maps!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn12" n="13">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mount Sonder, a peak in the MacDonnell ranges, NT, was named by Ernest Giles on his second expedition to central Australia, 1873-4. The name was included in Petermann’s publication of Giles’s sketch map as <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Originalkarte von E. Giles' Entdeckungsreise in Central-Australien, 1872, und Übersicht des Standpunktes der geographischen Kenntniss jener Gebiete</seg>, in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Petermann's geographische Mittheilungen</seg>, vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>19, 1873, published in May<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1873.  The National<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Library of Australia has digitized a copy:<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <ref target="https://protect-au.mimecast.com/s/pj29CYWLOxhMoWKZH0LSAb?domain=nla.gov.au">http://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232432495</ref>. The feature was included in later regional maps by Petermann, for example,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Die neuesten Entdeckungsreisen im Innern von Australien von Warburton, Giles, Forrest, April 1873-Sept. 1874</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1876) (digitized as <ref target="https://protect-au.mimecast.com/s/7HOuCZYMPyClnq1Rhj9FaP?domain=nla.gov.au">https://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232432276</ref>) and in the 1:3,500,000 scale<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Specialkarte von Australien in 9 Blättern nach originalen &amp; officiellen Quellen</seg> issued in 1875 (digitized as <ref target="https://protect-au.mimecast.com/s/sq7KC1WZKqh3wArmCp0d6e?domain=nla.gov.au">http://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-231345922</ref>),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but not in his 1:10,000,000<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>map of the whole of Australia, also issued in 1875 (digitized  as <ref target="https://protect-au.mimecast.com/s/sq7KC1WZKqh3wArmCp0d6e?domain=nla.gov.au">http://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232625532</ref>).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
